  "prompt": "Is it unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out on the counter overnight then refrigerated? Twice?",
  "response": "Yes, it is unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out on the counter overnight, even if it is later refrigerated. This is because perishable foods, like shrimp and fish, should not be left out at room temperature for more than two hours. Bacteria can grow rapidly between 40\u00b0F (4\u00b0C) and 140\u00b0F (60\u00b0C), a range known as the \"danger zone.\" Leaving these foods out overnight provides ample opportunity for bacteria to multiply to potentially dangerous levels, increasing the risk of foodborne illness.\n\nRefrigeration slows the growth of bacteria but it does not necessarily kill bacteria that may have already multiplied to unsafe levels. Repeating the process of leaving it out and refrigerating it again increases the risk even further. For safety reasons, it's best to discard shrimp or fish that has been left out overnight.",
